{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e41edb5e-793d-407e-a5b8-6b2705991994","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. CLI syntax changes\nMTP uses `--filter` but with **different operators**. The VSTest `~` (contains) operator becomes `contains`:\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest adapter, xUnit v2):\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP, xUnit v3):\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName contains IntegrationTests and Category = Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey operator translations:\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|--------|-----|\n| `~` | `contains` |\n| `&` | `and` |\n| `\\|` | `or` |\n| `!` | `not` |\n| `=` | `=` (same) |\n\n### 2. Missing runner reference\nYour `.csproj` sets `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner` but is missing the MTP runner package. You need to add it:\n\n```bash\ndotnet add package Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild\n```\n\nWithout it, `dotnet test` won't discover the MTP entry point correctly.\n\n### Summary\nYour updated CI command:\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName contains IntegrationTests and Category = Smoke\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1593f14a-675c-4ba4-8df9-a58204bcc7c5","outputTokens":327,"requestId":"5C33:852E1:B539B:E406D:69F54B8B"},"id":"df2cafbe-8efd-469c-8dbc-aafbe9e7a805","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:55:48.468Z","parentId":"cf533132-6778-431a-bf84-9450b5205ed0"}
